President Donald Trump issued a proclamation on National Manufacturing Day, expressing his commitment to restoring America's position as a global leader in manufacturing. He highlighted the revitalization of the manufacturing sector through economic and trade policies, research and development advancements, and the creation of a favorable environment for manufacturers and workers. The President also mentioned the renegotiation of NAFTA to benefit American manufacturing, the revision of the bilateral trade agreement with South Korea, and the strengthening of the defense industrial base. He emphasized the importance of investing in education and training for students and workers, as well as providing access to high-quality education in STEM fields. The proclamation acknowledged the challenges brought by technological advancements and called for the celebration of entrepreneurs, innovators, and workers in manufacturing.